OL,3,CVisually impaired veteran to run from
OL,4,CLands End and John O'Groats
OL,6,FA visually impaired veteran from West
OL,7,FCumbria is set to embark on a running
OL,8,Fchallenge between Lands End and John
OL,9,FO'Groats.
OL,11,FDarren Blanks from Egremont plans to
OL,12,Ffinish on Thursday 12 September and
OL,13,Fsays that if he completes it, it will
OL,14,Fmake him the first registered blind
OL,15,Fperson to do so.
OL,17,FHe is also deaf in his left ear and
OL,18,Fwill be joined by family and friends
OL,19,Fthroughout his time on the road,
OL,20,Fincluding by Gary McKee who ran a
OL,21,Fmarathon everyday for a year in 2022.
