OL,3,CVisually impaired veteran to run from
OL,4,CLands End and John O'Groats
OL,6,F"If the weather was different then
OL,7,Fwhat I would see would be different.
OL,8,FSometimes when I see a dark figure in
OL,9,Ffront of me I actually think it is a
OL,10,Fperson and I say thank you but it
OL,11,Fcould be a tree sometimes.
OL,13,F"Everyday is different and I have done
OL,14,Fit that long now that I'm used to it.
OL,15,FSometimes I don't say that I'm blind,
OL,16,FI just say that this is my vision."
OL,18,FDarren had previously served as a
OL,19,Fsoldier in the army and spent two
OL,20,Ftours in Iraq.
